thread.title: Arrest made in bank robbery

author: democratandchronicle.com
title: Arrest made in bank robbery
text:
Irondequoit Police have made an arrest in a bank robbery that happened Tuesday. Anthony Lucchese, 20, of Webster, has been charged with third-degree robbery and petty larceny. He is being held in the Monroe County Jail in lieu of $3,000 bail.
Lucchese is accused of robbing the ESL Federal Credit Union at 518 E. Ridge Road. He allegedly passed the teller a note and demanded money.
BLOUDON@Gannett.com
